1
00:00:03,003 --> 00:00:08,884
THE FLOWERS OF EVIL - BAUDELAIRE

2
00:00:08,967 --> 00:00:09,968
MIYAMA BOOKSTORE

3
00:00:10,052 --> 00:00:11,678
[Takao] <i>Dear Baudelaire,</i>

4
00:00:12,179 --> 00:00:14,014
<i>can you believe this?</i>

5
00:00:14,765 --> 00:00:16,475
<i>For the first time in my life,</i>

6
00:00:16,975 --> 00:00:18,810
<i>I'm witnessing with my own eyes,</i>

7
00:00:18,894 --> 00:00:20,687
<i>someone reading that book!</i>

8
00:00:25,859 --> 00:00:27,069
Tokiwa,

9
00:00:27,569 --> 00:00:28,654
that book...

10
00:00:29,780 --> 00:00:31,949
<i>The Flowers of Evil...</i> Why are you...?

11
00:00:32,032 --> 00:00:33,408
What's your problem?

12
00:00:33,492 --> 00:00:35,452
You're creeping me out.

13
00:00:35,536 --> 00:00:38,956
It's just... That book...

14
00:00:39,498 --> 00:00:41,792
I've never seen anyone reading it.

15
00:00:43,085 --> 00:00:44,586
Sorry.

16
00:00:45,337 --> 00:00:46,588
[Aya] Hey, wait a minute!

17
00:00:49,716 --> 00:00:50,717
SANITIZING WIPES

18
00:00:50,801 --> 00:00:52,052
Do you want one?

19
00:00:53,512 --> 00:00:55,764
Yeah, thanks.

20
00:00:59,977 --> 00:01:01,478
I'm surprised you know it.

21
00:01:01,561 --> 00:01:03,230
It's a pretty obscure book.

22
00:01:04,731 --> 00:01:06,191
When I was in junior high,

23
00:01:06,775 --> 00:01:08,735
I read it till the pages wore out.

24
00:01:09,570 --> 00:01:11,321
[chuckles softly] Impressive.

25
00:01:12,614 --> 00:01:13,824
Actually,

26
00:01:13,907 --> 00:01:15,867
a mystery novel I read recently

27
00:01:15,951 --> 00:01:18,370
used one of his poems to solve the trick.

28
00:01:18,870 --> 00:01:22,040
So, when I saw it on the shelf here,
I thought I'd take a look.

29
00:01:22,124 --> 00:01:24,084
Honestly, I don't really get it.

30
00:01:29,298 --> 00:01:32,009
You like books?

31
00:01:33,343 --> 00:01:34,553
I do...

32
00:01:35,554 --> 00:01:36,597
I mean, I did.

33
00:01:38,640 --> 00:01:40,434
I don't read at all now.

34
00:01:41,226 --> 00:01:42,227
Why not?

35
00:01:42,311 --> 00:01:43,770
Busy with club activities?

36
00:01:44,354 --> 00:01:45,480
[Takao] Well, no...

37
00:01:48,025 --> 00:01:49,109
Do you wanna read it?

38
00:01:50,319 --> 00:01:52,070
The mystery novel I mentioned.

39
00:01:53,196 --> 00:01:54,656
I just finished it.

40
00:02:20,349 --> 00:02:21,975
[sighs]

41
00:02:28,065 --> 00:02:30,067
[♪ gentle music playing]

42
00:02:54,925 --> 00:02:57,010
[♪ opening theme music playing]

43
00:03:52,649 --> 00:03:54,901
THE FLOWERS OF EVIL

44
00:03:54,985 --> 00:03:56,236
[Takao] Thanks for this.

45
00:03:56,361 --> 00:03:57,571
[Aya] You finished it already?

46
00:03:57,654 --> 00:03:58,655
EPISODE 9

47
00:03:58,738 --> 00:04:00,699
It was a really good book!

48
00:04:00,782 --> 00:04:03,785
I kept wondering what comes next.
I couldn't put it down.

49
00:04:04,286 --> 00:04:05,370
Right?

50
00:04:05,454 --> 00:04:08,165
There's a sequel, isn't there?

51
00:04:10,375 --> 00:04:11,418
[chuckles]

52
00:04:14,671 --> 00:04:16,381
[exclaims]

53
00:04:18,258 --> 00:04:19,301
Here.

54
00:04:19,384 --> 00:04:21,678
No way! Thank you.

55
00:04:22,554 --> 00:04:25,056
I kept wondering what happens
to the protagonist.

56
00:04:25,140 --> 00:04:29,561
To be honest, I couldn't concentrate
on my studies or anything.

57
00:04:29,644 --> 00:04:31,021
[laughing]

58
00:04:31,104 --> 00:04:33,106
[laughter echoes]

59
00:04:36,359 --> 00:04:37,778
I know, right?

60
00:04:38,445 --> 00:04:40,989
Hey, let me borrow one of your books, too.

61
00:04:41,448 --> 00:04:42,616
Ah.

62
00:04:42,699 --> 00:04:44,785
Nothing like <i>The Flowers of Evil,</i> please.

63
00:04:45,452 --> 00:04:49,289
Got anything more serious,
with substance, and fun to read?

64
00:04:50,791 --> 00:04:54,169
I got rid of all my books
when we moved here.

65
00:04:54,669 --> 00:04:56,379
Just give me the titles, then.

66
00:04:56,463 --> 00:04:58,173
You used to read a lot, right?

67
00:05:05,514 --> 00:05:06,556
Takao!

68
00:05:07,057 --> 00:05:09,184
How you doin' these days? Everything good?

69
00:05:09,684 --> 00:05:10,852
Now, listen.

70
00:05:11,353 --> 00:05:13,897
Don't worry your mother, you understand?

71
00:05:13,980 --> 00:05:17,192
Hey! Go take a bath already!

72
00:05:17,275 --> 00:05:19,319
-What'd you say?!
-[Shizue groans]

73
00:05:19,402 --> 00:05:21,154
Don't nag me like that.

74
00:05:21,238 --> 00:05:23,532
I've been working all day, you know.

75
00:05:23,615 --> 00:05:26,034
[Shizue] And I do the housework
on top of a part-time job.

76
00:05:26,535 --> 00:05:29,037
[Tetsuo] Well,
I'm sorry I get paid peanuts.

77
00:05:29,120 --> 00:05:31,373
Do you think I want to be in this job?!

78
00:05:31,456 --> 00:05:34,042
[Shizue] Here we go again...

79
00:05:34,125 --> 00:05:35,126
What's that?!

80
00:05:35,210 --> 00:05:36,628
[indistinct chatter]

81
00:05:39,506 --> 00:05:40,507
[Takao] Here.

82
00:05:41,383 --> 00:05:44,135
-[Aya] Wow.
-[♪ pleasant music playing]

83
00:05:44,219 --> 00:05:49,307
Tsutsui? I like his work, too.
You like <i>Erotic Avenue?</i>

84
00:05:49,391 --> 00:05:52,978
I liked
<i>Lagos on a Journey</i> better. [chuckles]

85
00:05:53,061 --> 00:05:55,397
[chuckles awkwardly] Sorry.

86
00:05:56,398 --> 00:05:57,399
What?

87
00:05:58,024 --> 00:06:00,902
Why are you apologizing? [laughing]

88
00:06:01,695 --> 00:06:03,029
You're silly.

89
00:06:11,162 --> 00:06:12,539
[grunts]

90
00:06:15,333 --> 00:06:16,793
[Takao] Thanks for lending it to me.

91
00:06:17,460 --> 00:06:19,170
It was really interesting.

92
00:06:19,254 --> 00:06:21,423
[Aya exclaims] This is from me, then.

93
00:06:21,506 --> 00:06:22,507
Here.

94
00:06:23,174 --> 00:06:25,051
-I told you it's not.
-[chuckles]

95
00:06:25,135 --> 00:06:26,469
Is that Kasuga over there?

96
00:06:26,553 --> 00:06:28,471
-[Tamaru] What?
-What's he doing?

97
00:06:29,014 --> 00:06:30,056
[Tamaru] He's reading a book.

98
00:06:30,140 --> 00:06:32,309
[Sasaki] That's not like him.

99
00:06:34,853 --> 00:06:37,647
THE METAMORPHOSIS X KAFKA
TRANSLATION BY YOSHITAKA TAKAHASHI

100
00:06:40,483 --> 00:06:42,402
[Aya] I read it, but,

101
00:06:42,485 --> 00:06:44,946
you sure have terrible taste!

102
00:06:45,030 --> 00:06:47,073
[chuckles awkwardly] Sorry about that.

103
00:06:47,157 --> 00:06:50,619
That unsettling feeling that
maybe people are really like this.

104
00:06:50,702 --> 00:06:56,583
Right... I see your point.
You... think so?

105
00:06:56,666 --> 00:07:00,253
Come on! You're the one
who recommended it to me!

106
00:07:01,004 --> 00:07:03,798
You have to get it together!

107
00:07:03,882 --> 00:07:06,926
You're the only one
I can talk to about books.

108
00:07:08,970 --> 00:07:10,096
Sorry.

109
00:07:11,139 --> 00:07:12,932
[laughter echoes]

110
00:07:16,770 --> 00:07:20,106
Kasuga, we saw you yesterday.
Getting some alone time with Tokiwa.

111
00:07:20,607 --> 00:07:23,652
No, that's not...
I was just borrowing a book from her.

112
00:07:23,735 --> 00:07:26,029
Too bad, Kasuga.

113
00:07:26,112 --> 00:07:27,906
Tokiwa has a boyfriend!

114
00:07:27,989 --> 00:07:32,118
I heard he's a third year at North High,
and they met at her part-time job!

115
00:07:32,202 --> 00:07:34,829
What a fleeting romance
it was for you, Kasuga.

116
00:07:34,913 --> 00:07:37,415
We won't let you get ahead of us.
Right, guys?

117
00:07:37,499 --> 00:07:41,127
-[boys laughing]
-Come on, it's not like that.

118
00:07:41,211 --> 00:07:43,046
[boys] Mmm.

119
00:07:43,129 --> 00:07:46,132
[Takao] <i>What are you doing,</i>
<i>trying to build relationships with people?</i>

120
00:07:46,883 --> 00:07:49,386
<i>Have you forgotten what you did?</i>

121
00:07:50,011 --> 00:07:51,262
<i>You shit bug!</i>

122
00:07:52,889 --> 00:07:53,890
Hey ya.

123
00:07:57,602 --> 00:07:59,312
Thanks for letting me borrow these.

124
00:07:59,396 --> 00:08:00,855
Weren't they great?

125
00:08:00,939 --> 00:08:03,274
I think they're the best
of the whole series.

126
00:08:03,775 --> 00:08:04,776
Yeah.

127
00:08:06,069 --> 00:08:08,279
What? You didn't care for them?

128
00:08:08,363 --> 00:08:11,700
That's not it at all!
I can't wait to read the rest.

129
00:08:13,201 --> 00:08:14,536
I'm sorry.

130
00:08:14,619 --> 00:08:18,331
I stayed at a friends' house last night,
so I don't have the next volume.

131
00:08:19,874 --> 00:08:21,292
Your friends' house...

132
00:08:22,419 --> 00:08:23,503
Of course.

133
00:08:23,586 --> 00:08:27,424
[laughing] Wait, what is this?
Are you that bummed about it?

134
00:08:28,717 --> 00:08:31,386
Wanna come over to my house to get it?

135
00:08:31,970 --> 00:08:32,971
What?!

136
00:08:33,471 --> 00:08:34,848
[Kanami] There you are!

137
00:08:34,931 --> 00:08:36,683
Tokiwa!

138
00:08:38,810 --> 00:08:40,687
Why don't you come to this with us?

139
00:08:40,770 --> 00:08:42,522
[Aya] Sorry, I have plans today.

140
00:08:42,605 --> 00:08:45,358
Okay, then. We'll see you tomorrow.

141
00:08:45,442 --> 00:08:46,526
-Yeah.
-See you.

142
00:08:46,609 --> 00:08:48,319
-Bye.
-Bye-bye.

143
00:08:48,987 --> 00:08:50,321
Who was that next to her?

144
00:08:50,405 --> 00:08:53,199
-[Yuki] No clue.
-[Kanami] Off we go, off we go.

145
00:08:53,283 --> 00:08:54,534
[Aya] Let's go.

146
00:08:54,617 --> 00:08:55,994
Okay, sure.

147
00:08:56,077 --> 00:08:58,955
TOKIWA

148
00:09:01,916 --> 00:09:03,543
[Aya] You can relax, you know.

149
00:09:04,169 --> 00:09:08,339
Well, I mean...
I'll leave as soon as I borrow the book.

150
00:09:08,840 --> 00:09:11,384
[Aya] Where did I put that one...

151
00:09:15,055 --> 00:09:16,222
What?

152
00:09:17,766 --> 00:09:18,975
This is amazing!

153
00:09:21,061 --> 00:09:24,105
Hey, don't gawk at it like that.

154
00:09:24,189 --> 00:09:28,109
[Takao] I don't mean to, but...
You've read all of these books, right?

155
00:09:28,193 --> 00:09:30,612
You must really love to read.

156
00:09:31,696 --> 00:09:32,822
It really is amazing.

157
00:09:32,906 --> 00:09:35,075
Stop it already. [chuckles]

158
00:09:37,702 --> 00:09:40,163
PLOT

159
00:09:47,629 --> 00:09:48,713
[gasps]

160
00:09:48,797 --> 00:09:50,632
[♪ gentle music playing]

161
00:09:51,966 --> 00:09:53,802
What is that?

162
00:09:54,552 --> 00:09:56,930
It's nothing.

163
00:09:57,972 --> 00:09:59,057
By any chance...

164
00:09:59,557 --> 00:10:01,601
Is it a novel you wrote?

165
00:10:01,684 --> 00:10:02,727
No, it isn't.

166
00:10:04,938 --> 00:10:06,147
Can't I take a peek?

167
00:10:06,231 --> 00:10:08,108
I'm telling you it's not!

168
00:10:25,083 --> 00:10:26,459
[phone vibrating]

169
00:10:32,757 --> 00:10:34,008
Hello?

170
00:10:35,468 --> 00:10:38,096
What? Wait a second, it's nothing like--

171
00:10:38,888 --> 00:10:39,889
What?

172
00:10:47,730 --> 00:10:48,940
Kasuga,

173
00:10:49,691 --> 00:10:50,692
I'm sorry.

174
00:10:51,651 --> 00:10:52,986
My boyfriend's here.

175
00:10:55,321 --> 00:10:56,322
What?

176
00:10:57,282 --> 00:10:59,325
[dog barking]

177
00:11:03,580 --> 00:11:05,248
Thanks for waiting, Koji.

178
00:11:07,876 --> 00:11:09,711
This is Kasuga.

179
00:11:11,379 --> 00:11:12,380
Hello.

180
00:11:14,924 --> 00:11:16,467
[laughing]

181
00:11:16,551 --> 00:11:20,388
No way! I wondered what stud you'd taken
into your room, but this guy?

182
00:11:20,471 --> 00:11:21,848
Well... I'm...

183
00:11:22,432 --> 00:11:24,058
I'm sorry, sir.

184
00:11:24,142 --> 00:11:25,143
[scoffs]

185
00:11:25,226 --> 00:11:28,771
It's obvious you don't have
the guts to do anything.

186
00:11:28,855 --> 00:11:31,191
Hey, wanna go to our usual spot?

187
00:11:31,274 --> 00:11:32,817
We can get pizza or something.

188
00:11:32,901 --> 00:11:35,320
Sounds good. Let's go.

189
00:11:37,238 --> 00:11:40,325
[stammers] I'm really, truly sorry.

190
00:11:41,951 --> 00:11:43,286
Hey.

191
00:11:44,996 --> 00:11:48,499
Come with us, Kasuga.

192
00:11:48,583 --> 00:11:49,584
What?

193
00:11:53,004 --> 00:11:54,923
[♪ techno music playing]

194
00:12:02,847 --> 00:12:04,682
Wanna go clubbing? A sick DJ's coming.

195
00:12:04,766 --> 00:12:05,850
-Really?
-For real?

196
00:12:05,934 --> 00:12:07,101
We're in!

197
00:12:07,185 --> 00:12:08,186
That's so cool!

198
00:12:08,269 --> 00:12:10,480
[male student 1] We have to go!
Promise, okay?

199
00:12:10,563 --> 00:12:13,524
Hey, you haven't eaten at all.

200
00:12:13,608 --> 00:12:16,069
Go ahead, have some!

201
00:12:16,819 --> 00:12:20,240
-Thank you. I'll take this.
-Sure!

202
00:12:29,707 --> 00:12:33,002
-Dude, you've got cheese right here.
-[all laughing]

203
00:12:33,086 --> 00:12:34,420
-Come on, man.
-Damn.

204
00:12:34,504 --> 00:12:36,089
[female student 1] You're way too nervous.

205
00:12:36,172 --> 00:12:38,258
See? I told you he's funny.

206
00:12:38,967 --> 00:12:41,761
Kasuga, was it? Are you in any clubs?

207
00:12:41,844 --> 00:12:43,805
Wait, wait. I wanna guess.

208
00:12:46,182 --> 00:12:47,183
The Going-Home Club.

209
00:12:48,810 --> 00:12:49,811
That's correct.

210
00:12:49,894 --> 00:12:50,895
[male student 2] I knew it!

211
00:12:50,979 --> 00:12:54,023
Hey, I know.
I bet you're hobby is "reading."

212
00:12:54,107 --> 00:12:55,233
Right?

213
00:12:55,900 --> 00:12:59,153
-[female student 2] Man, you're terrible!
-[all laughing]

214
00:12:59,237 --> 00:13:01,489
How about... a girlfriend?

215
00:13:01,572 --> 00:13:03,324
I bet he doesn't have one!

216
00:13:03,408 --> 00:13:04,742
[female student 3] You're so mean!

217
00:13:04,826 --> 00:13:06,869
So, what's the answer?

218
00:13:08,037 --> 00:13:09,872
-I don't have one.
-[male student 3] Knew it!

219
00:13:09,956 --> 00:13:11,124
So, you're a virgin.

220
00:13:11,207 --> 00:13:13,876
[female student 4] Takuya!
You have no filter!

221
00:13:14,961 --> 00:13:17,255
Do you have a crush on anyone right now?

222
00:13:18,548 --> 00:13:19,549
No,

223
00:13:20,049 --> 00:13:21,050
not in particular.

224
00:13:21,634 --> 00:13:25,638
Come on,
tell us more about yourself, Kasuga!

225
00:13:26,597 --> 00:13:28,725
Okay, then.

226
00:13:28,808 --> 00:13:31,644
The name of your crush from junior high!

227
00:13:31,728 --> 00:13:33,563
[all exclaiming]

228
00:13:33,646 --> 00:13:37,483
Three, two, one, go!

229
00:13:40,695 --> 00:13:42,321
[chuckles] Go!

230
00:13:47,827 --> 00:13:49,287
I don't want to say.

231
00:13:50,580 --> 00:13:53,833
What does it matter, though?
It's in the past.

232
00:13:53,916 --> 00:13:55,126
Cut it out, Koji.

233
00:13:55,835 --> 00:13:57,128
All right, then.

234
00:13:57,628 --> 00:14:00,006
How did you get acquainted with Aya?

235
00:14:00,089 --> 00:14:02,675
-We were at karaoke together.
-I didn't ask you, Aya.

236
00:14:02,759 --> 00:14:04,177
Right, Kasuga?

237
00:14:05,094 --> 00:14:06,304
Tell me.

238
00:14:06,387 --> 00:14:09,474
How did things turn out
that you became close with Aya?

239
00:14:10,433 --> 00:14:11,434
Well, I mean...

240
00:14:11,517 --> 00:14:15,396
How did things turn out
that you ended up going to Aya's room?

241
00:14:16,355 --> 00:14:17,732
-What? No way.
-Seriously?

242
00:14:17,815 --> 00:14:20,234
[Koji] I haven't
stepped foot in there, not once.

243
00:14:20,318 --> 00:14:23,237
No matter how many times I asked,

244
00:14:23,321 --> 00:14:25,615
she'd always say,
"I don't ever let anyone in!"

245
00:14:26,157 --> 00:14:27,241
Isn't that right, Aya?

246
00:14:27,950 --> 00:14:29,911
-It's not like that.
-So...

247
00:14:30,411 --> 00:14:32,622
Why do you get to just waltz in?

248
00:14:33,122 --> 00:14:34,832
Why? Tell me!

249
00:14:34,916 --> 00:14:36,167
Stop it.

250
00:14:36,250 --> 00:14:37,335
What?

251
00:14:38,419 --> 00:14:40,421
Am I the one who's out of line?

252
00:14:51,390 --> 00:14:52,975
I'm sorry.

253
00:14:55,895 --> 00:14:57,897
I really had no intentions of

254
00:14:58,773 --> 00:15:00,691
doing anything with Tokiwa.

255
00:15:02,401 --> 00:15:03,402
I was just...

256
00:15:04,153 --> 00:15:05,571
just happy.

257
00:15:06,781 --> 00:15:09,367
It's been a really long time
since I've made a friend.

258
00:15:10,868 --> 00:15:11,869
So...

259
00:15:12,662 --> 00:15:14,122
I got carried away.

260
00:15:15,832 --> 00:15:17,959
<i>I forgot about what kind of person I am.</i>

261
00:15:18,042 --> 00:15:19,877
[♪ gentle music playing]

262
00:15:20,461 --> 00:15:21,587
I forgot

263
00:15:22,296 --> 00:15:24,715
that I'm just a ghost
who causes trouble for people.

264
00:15:26,217 --> 00:15:27,385
A ghost?

265
00:15:28,845 --> 00:15:32,181
I will make sure it never happens again.

266
00:15:33,266 --> 00:15:34,308
Not ever.

267
00:15:35,726 --> 00:15:36,978
I swear.

268
00:15:48,197 --> 00:15:49,198
Hey.

269
00:15:52,743 --> 00:15:54,787
We've been together for a whole year.

270
00:15:55,329 --> 00:15:56,372
So...

271
00:15:57,081 --> 00:15:59,417
why do you still have your walls up?

272
00:16:00,459 --> 00:16:01,669
Then,

273
00:16:02,587 --> 00:16:06,799
have you tried
to tear down those walls for me?

274
00:16:11,637 --> 00:16:14,432
You're empty, Koji.

275
00:16:21,647 --> 00:16:25,568
[Takao] <i>Look what you did! Once again,</i>
<i>you got involved and hurt people!</i>

276
00:16:26,068 --> 00:16:30,031
<i>I haven't learned anything, after all.</i>
<i>Just repeating the same mistakes.</i>

277
00:16:30,114 --> 00:16:31,616
Kasuga!

278
00:16:34,368 --> 00:16:35,494
I'm sorry about that.

279
00:16:36,954 --> 00:16:37,997
Don't be.

280
00:16:39,332 --> 00:16:42,251
I shouldn't have gone to your house.

281
00:16:44,503 --> 00:16:46,422
It's not your fault, Kasuga.

282
00:16:53,471 --> 00:16:55,223
At the end of the day,

283
00:16:56,474 --> 00:16:57,808
I'm empty, too.

284
00:16:59,769 --> 00:17:01,145
I guess...

285
00:17:01,771 --> 00:17:03,606
I was trying too hard, you know?

286
00:17:05,900 --> 00:17:07,985
Being with Koji and those guys...

287
00:17:08,819 --> 00:17:11,197
It doesn't mean I can become like them.

288
00:17:15,743 --> 00:17:16,744
The thing is...

289
00:17:17,536 --> 00:17:18,996
I've never told anyone.

290
00:17:20,915 --> 00:17:22,541
That I liked books.

291
00:17:23,834 --> 00:17:24,877
Why not?

292
00:17:28,506 --> 00:17:31,425
Because they'll freak out, for sure.

293
00:17:32,009 --> 00:17:33,928
A room filled with books like that?

294
00:17:34,595 --> 00:17:35,596
It's weird.

295
00:17:35,680 --> 00:17:37,056
It's not weird at all!

296
00:17:39,267 --> 00:17:40,393
I...

297
00:17:41,269 --> 00:17:42,395
I think...

298
00:17:42,478 --> 00:17:44,105
[♪ gentle music playing]

299
00:17:44,188 --> 00:17:45,773
I honestly think...

300
00:17:46,732 --> 00:17:48,734
you're incredible, Tokiwa.

301
00:17:50,653 --> 00:17:51,696
So...

302
00:17:53,656 --> 00:17:55,074
So, I...

303
00:17:57,952 --> 00:17:59,328
I want to read it.

304
00:17:59,829 --> 00:18:01,539
The novel you wrote.

305
00:18:06,919 --> 00:18:08,087
Ah.

306
00:18:08,963 --> 00:18:10,172
I'm sorry.

307
00:18:10,256 --> 00:18:11,591
I did it again...

308
00:18:13,926 --> 00:18:14,927
Okay.

309
00:18:16,596 --> 00:18:17,930
Read it.

310
00:18:18,639 --> 00:18:19,890
I want you to read it.

311
00:18:22,393 --> 00:18:25,563
I want you to read that notebook, Kasuga.

312
00:18:30,026 --> 00:18:32,862
[muffled singing]

313
00:18:37,116 --> 00:18:39,493
Why are we in a karaoke box?

314
00:18:41,912 --> 00:18:44,332
I can't risk having someone see us.

315
00:18:47,293 --> 00:18:48,336
Let me read it.

316
00:18:49,629 --> 00:18:50,671
Not yet!

317
00:18:52,673 --> 00:18:56,886
I mean, I still only have the synopsis.

318
00:18:56,969 --> 00:18:59,472
Like, it's just a rough outline.

319
00:19:06,979 --> 00:19:08,189
Nevermind.

320
00:19:10,858 --> 00:19:12,943
Give me...

321
00:19:14,028 --> 00:19:15,279
your honest opinion.

322
00:19:17,573 --> 00:19:18,699
Sure.

323
00:19:22,953 --> 00:19:25,498
PLOT

324
00:19:26,123 --> 00:19:29,835
POTENTIAL TITLE
THE GHOST MURDER CASE (TENTATIVE)

325
00:19:29,919 --> 00:19:31,170
Ghost...

326
00:19:38,386 --> 00:19:40,429
SCENE: A VILLAGE IN THE MOUNTAINS

327
00:19:43,849 --> 00:19:46,060
GHOST SIGHTINGS AT A MANOR
WHERE THE STORY BEGINS

328
00:19:46,143 --> 00:19:48,521
PROTAGONIST
A HIGH SCHOOL BOY STUCK IN THE VILLAGE

329
00:19:48,604 --> 00:19:53,818
BEST HITS OF 2001

330
00:19:53,901 --> 00:19:55,486
[♪ eerie music playing]

331
00:19:55,569 --> 00:20:00,366
[Aya] <i>I'll just live on here forever,</i>
<i>feeling like I'm dead.</i>

332
00:20:00,908 --> 00:20:02,493
<i>That's what I thought.</i>

333
00:20:04,495 --> 00:20:07,164
<i>That's when the incident happened.</i>

334
00:20:08,499 --> 00:20:11,794
<i>Several people vanished into thin air.</i>

335
00:20:13,629 --> 00:20:18,134
<i>Everyone rumored</i>
<i>that it was the ghost's doing.</i>

336
00:20:18,676 --> 00:20:19,677
<i>But...</i>

337
00:20:20,177 --> 00:20:22,346
<i>That's not a ghost.</i>

338
00:20:24,432 --> 00:20:27,810
<i>I have to discover the identity.</i>

339
00:20:27,893 --> 00:20:29,645
[wind howling]

340
00:20:31,355 --> 00:20:34,066
<i>Who is behind this incident?</i>

341
00:20:39,572 --> 00:20:41,991
<i>I have to figure it out...</i>

342
00:20:46,245 --> 00:20:48,247
<i>to put an end to living like a ghost.</i>

343
00:21:10,603 --> 00:21:12,104
[♪ music swells]

344
00:21:15,941 --> 00:21:17,276
[♪ music fades]

345
00:21:25,326 --> 00:21:27,077
Sorry, forget it!

346
00:21:27,703 --> 00:21:28,746
Tokiwa...

347
00:21:30,164 --> 00:21:31,332
This is amazing!

348
00:21:34,585 --> 00:21:36,879
Surrounded by mountains,

349
00:21:37,546 --> 00:21:38,839
stuck with nowhere to go,

350
00:21:39,507 --> 00:21:40,758
nothing to do...

351
00:21:42,009 --> 00:21:43,636
I know this protagonist.

352
00:21:45,262 --> 00:21:46,680
He's the same as me!

353
00:21:48,015 --> 00:21:51,560
But he takes on the challenge
of solving this case.

354
00:21:52,520 --> 00:21:54,271
No one could come up with this.

355
00:21:54,980 --> 00:21:56,357
It really is amazing!

356
00:21:57,691 --> 00:21:59,151
It's fascinating!

357
00:21:59,652 --> 00:22:00,861
I can't wait to read it!

358
00:22:01,362 --> 00:22:02,863
Please write it!

359
00:22:02,947 --> 00:22:04,824
[♪ gentle music playing]

360
00:22:08,410 --> 00:22:09,495
Thank you.

361
00:22:10,162 --> 00:22:12,540
I'll try writing it!

362
00:22:13,290 --> 00:22:14,291
Yeah.

363
00:22:18,587 --> 00:22:20,798
There's no time to waste!

364
00:22:20,881 --> 00:22:22,633
I have to start writing, fast!

365
00:22:23,175 --> 00:22:25,135
I already thought of the first scene.

366
00:22:25,219 --> 00:22:28,055
It's the sight of the people
who went missing.

367
00:22:28,138 --> 00:22:30,891
[chuckles] That sounds great.
It's so exciting.

368
00:22:30,975 --> 00:22:34,353
If you don't mind,
would you read it as I go?

369
00:22:34,436 --> 00:22:35,437
Are you sure?

370
00:22:35,521 --> 00:22:37,147
-Yes.
-[chuckles]

371
00:22:40,442 --> 00:22:43,654
[Takao] <i>It smells like... shampoo.</i>

372
00:22:43,737 --> 00:22:45,948
[♪ suspenseful music playing]

373
00:22:51,120 --> 00:22:53,372
[♪ closing theme music playing]

374
00:22:53,455 --> 00:22:54,999
Kasuga?

375
00:22:56,917 --> 00:22:58,085
Saeki...

376
00:23:07,428 --> 00:23:09,305
[indistinct chatter]

377
00:23:10,723 --> 00:23:13,058
TO BE CONTINUED

378
00:23:47,927 --> 00:23:48,969
ON THE NEXT EPISODE

379
00:23:49,053 --> 00:23:52,723
[narrator] <i>After an unexpected reunion</i>
<i>with Saeki, Kasuga flees once again.</i>

380
00:23:52,806 --> 00:23:56,101
<i>Still, he finally decides</i>
<i>to face his own shadows.</i>

381
00:23:56,185 --> 00:23:58,354
<i>Next, on episode ten,</i>

382
00:23:58,437 --> 00:24:01,607
<i>Kasuga's feelings for her begin to bloom.</i>

383
00:24:01,690 --> 00:24:02,900
Translated by Yuka Kristi
